T1  - Foreign Competition, Market Power, and Wage Inequality*
PY  - 1995
Y1  - 1995/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2946649
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 110
IS  - 4
SP  - 1075
EP  - 1110
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper investigates the link between the trend in the returns to education and foreign competition in concentrated industries. We argue that the impact of foreign competition on the relative wages of less skilled workers depends on the market structure of the industry penetrated. The empirical evidence indicates that employment changes in a small group of trade-impacted concentrated industries can explain not only part of the aggregate rise in wage inequality in the United States, but also some of the differences in the trends in wage inequality across metropolitan areas.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2946649
